		<a href="MB_editmsg.asp?FID=73&FN=Wizard&SID=7&SN=EverQuest&TID=2020786&TN=A+New+Wizard&CAT=Classes&SURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eeverlore%2Ecom&MSID=2077295&PL=4">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif" border="0" alt="Edit/Delete Message" width="18" height="13"></a>
		
		</font>
		<hr size="1">First, no I'm not being mean just don't want you to get messed with later.  A "sorcerer" in this game is a Mage, we're not that.  Just a little bit of uselesss information.</P><P>Next, While agro management is key, also balancing your equipment is also very important.  There is alot of high INT or high Mana gear out there with no AC, skip all this junk.  You will draw agro, you will get hit, so make sure you have some decent AC.  To start the game, Netted Kelp is some of the best twinking gear around for the AC/INT/STA mix.  Just remember to take it off before you buy or sell.  Also remember that in the beginning (until lvl 30) a Moonstone Ring will give more Mana than a 6 INT ring, so buy accordingly.</P><P>Lastly, as I have just realized, Focus Effects are your friend in a big way.  One of your best investments will be the Blackened Alloy Medalion for it's mana conservation effect.  It has very good stats and saving mana is huge.  I just changed out for this, an improved damage 2 item and an extanded range 2 item and the loss of mana is by far offset by the improvements I got for them.</P><P>Dex has no effect on spell casting criticals (I wasn't sure until recently) so don't waste time there.  But get a decent 1hb or piercing weapon to kill that MOB after it turns and starts to run to save mana for the next victim.</P><P>Good luck.</P><P>Stryf <BR>lvl 39 High Elf Wizard</P><P>Vildaar Darkmender<BR>lcl 62 DE Cleric<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
