		<hr size="1">Ac is nice for exp groups. But with proper agro manegment you can due significant amounts of dmg and never draw agro away from the tank ever. At the higher lvls if you draw agro away from the MT you die, then just about everyone else dies because after you drop the raid mob heads strait for the healers. Balancing your equipment is nice, but if you can;t control agro it willb e harder for you to lvl, which makes it harder to get in on the good raides for good equipment. So basically agro management is a keey skill that will effect your entire life as a wizard. </P><P>I also agree make sure you don't neglect any of your casting skills. There is nothing worsde then fizzling an entire bar of mana trying to summon your familiar.</P><P><font size=+2 face="Impact" color="blue"><i>Azurewrath Mythryn</i></font><br><font size=+1 face="chiller" color="red">Arcanist of Solusek Ro</font><br>Vallon Zek <br><blockquote><i>"A wizard is never late, nor is he ever early. He arrives precisely when he means to"<br>         -Gandalf Stormcrow<i></hr></blockquote><br></P><P><br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
